      "title": "Identifying Types of Gangs",
      "content": "Understanding the various types of gangs is essential for grasping the complexities of gang culture. Here are key types to recognize:\n- **Street Gangs**: Local groups involved in criminal activities and turf wars.\n- **Prison Gangs**: Formed within correctional facilities, often for protection and control.\n- **Motorcycle Gangs**: Organized groups with a focus on motorcycle culture, sometimes involved in criminal enterprises.\n- **Youth Gangs**: Often composed of younger individuals, engaging in delinquent behavior and seeking identity.\n\nRecognizing these categories helps in understanding the broader implications of gang culture."
